issue.body:
I've also reduced some code duplication. The broken test was actually this:

```
      check_eq(collect(range(1, 2)
                         .concat(obs_error(sec::runtime_error))
                         .on_error_return([](const error& what) {
                           return expected<int>{what};
                         })
                         .take(2)),
```

Calling `take(2)` here will means the observer cuts off the subscription after receiving `2`. So this was actually a bug before that I didn't spot during the review. So merging the recent PR actually fixed a bug and this test should've never worked.

